cinder/volume/flows/manager/create_volum.message:
-1: While the code change works and fixes the problem, I believe there is a slightly better solution.  We should just return the new size in the model_update.  That way we avoid an additional DB write.

With current code:

- DB call here: Save size
- DB call done on the caller that receives the model_update: Saves the rest of the model update if no size was present, and if size was present (the bug PowerFlex is experiencing) it saves the rest of the model and the size (again).

I think this would be better:

                    if model_update:
                        model_update['size'] = original_size
                    else:
                        model_update = {'size': original_size}

there's also this other alternative which I don't like as much:

                    if model_update:
                        model_update['size'] = original_size
                    else:
                        volume.size = original_size
                        volume.save()
